Package eu.advance.logistics.flow.engine.error

Compilation error classes.

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    HasBinding
    Interface to represent an error having the reference to a specific binding.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CombinedTypeError
    The combination (e.g., union) of two types could not be created.
    ConcreteVsParametricTypeError
    The wire binds a concrete type and a parametric type which cannot be in subtype relation.
    ConstantOutputError
    A wire is bound to a constant on its destination side.
    DestinationToCompositeInputError
    The wire's destination is bound to an input port of the parent composite block's.
    DestinationToCompositeOutputError
    The wire's destination is bound to an output port of a composite block (not the parent block).
    DestinationToOutputError
    The wire's destination is bound to an output port of a block.
    ErrorLookup
    Utility class to store and manage creator functions for various compilation error classes.
    GeneralCompilationError
    A general compilation error indicator when the error details are stored in XML.
    IncompatibleBaseTypesError
    The wire binds two parametric types which have incompatible base types or number of arguments.
    IncompatibleTypesError
    The wire binds two concrete types where the left type does not extend or equals to the right type.
    MissingBlockError
    The referenced block type cannot be found.
    MissingDestinationError
    The destination object of the binding cannot be found.
    MissingDestinationPortError
    The destination port of the destination object cannot be found.
    MissingSourceError
    The source object of the binding cannot be found.
    MissingSourcePortError
    The source port of the source object cannot be found.
    MultiInputBindingError
    An input port is bound to multiple outputs at the same time.
    SourceToCompositeInputError
    The source (input) of the binding points to a composite input port in the same level (and not the parent composite's input).
    SourceToCompositeOutputError
    The source of the binding points to the output port of the enclosing composite's output port.
    SourceToInputBindingError
    The wire's source is bound to an input port of an block.
    TypeArgumentCountError
    The wire binds two parametric types with different type argument count.
    TypeMismatchError
    Type inference error on the given wire.
